message.text:
𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐯𝐞𝐥 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐈𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭: 𝐕𝐨𝐥𝐮𝐧𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐋𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐖𝐚𝐲! ✈️🌏

𝐖𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐝 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐃𝐚𝐲 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓 presents 𝐕𝐨𝐥𝐮𝐧𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐢𝐧 𝐀𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧, an exciting event centered on the theme “𝐄𝐦𝐩𝐨𝐰𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐕𝐨𝐥𝐮𝐧𝐭𝐞𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐚 𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐧𝐬𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐯𝐞 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐅𝐮𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞.” This event highlights how volunteer efforts can create meaningful change in communities and travel experiences worldwide.

Be part of the movement that combines passion for travel with a commitment to giving back. This is your chance to learn, connect, and take action for responsible tourism that uplifts lives and preserves cultures.

Register now and step into a journey where your time and skills make a lasting difference, PATAms! 

🗓️: 𝐒𝐞𝐩𝐭𝐞𝐦𝐛𝐞𝐫 𝟐𝟐, 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓
🕰️: 𝟏:𝟑𝟎 𝐩𝐦 - 𝟒:𝟑𝟎 𝐩𝐦 
📍: 𝐒𝐜𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞 𝐁𝐮𝐢𝐥𝐝𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝟏𝟎𝟐 - 𝟏𝟎𝟒

𝐑𝐞𝐠𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐋𝐢𝐧𝐤:
https://forms.gle/8TrXYkVziu7W7oGL8

𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐯𝐞𝐥 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐈𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐭: 𝐕𝐨𝐥𝐮𝐧𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐋𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐖𝐚𝐲! ✈️🌏

𝐖𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐝 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐃𝐚𝐲 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓 presents 𝐕𝐨𝐥𝐮𝐧𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐢𝐧 𝐀𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧, an exciting event centered on the theme “𝐄𝐦𝐩𝐨𝐰𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐕𝐨𝐥𝐮𝐧𝐭𝐞𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐚 𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐧𝐬𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐯𝐞 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐅𝐮𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞.” This event highlights how volunteer efforts can create meaningful change in communities and travel experiences worldwide.

Be part of the movement that combines passion for travel with a commitment to giving back. This is your chance to learn, connect, and take action for responsible tourism that uplifts lives and preserves cultures.

Register now and step into a journey where your time and skills make a lasting difference, PATAms! 

🗓️: 𝐒𝐞𝐩𝐭𝐞𝐦𝐛𝐞𝐫 𝟐𝟐, 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓
🕰️: 𝟏:𝟑𝟎 𝐩𝐦 - 𝟒:𝟑𝟎 𝐩𝐦 
📍: 𝐒𝐜𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞 𝐁𝐮𝐢𝐥𝐝𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝟏𝟎𝟐 - 𝟏𝟎𝟒

𝐑𝐞𝐠𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐋𝐢𝐧𝐤:
https://forms.gle/8TrXYkVziu7W7oGL8

In partnership with:
FEU ITHM Music Makers
FEU Sexuality and Gender Alliance

𝐖𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐝 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐃𝐚𝐲 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓 presents 𝐕𝐨𝐥𝐮𝐧𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐢𝐧 𝐀𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧, an exciting event centered on the theme “𝐄𝐦𝐩𝐨𝐰𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐕𝐨𝐥𝐮𝐧𝐭𝐞𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐚 𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐧𝐬𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐯𝐞 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐅𝐮𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞.” This event highlights how volunteer efforts can create meaningful change in communities and travel experiences worldwide.

Register now and step into a journey where your time and skills make a lasting difference, PATAms!

message.text:
UE Advisory
for Sept. 18 & 19, 2025

In light of the announced transport strike, please be advised of the following modalities for this Thursday and Friday, September 18 and 19, 2025 —

Graduate School and College of Law: Online modality for Thursday and Friday

CDent: Doctor of Dental Medicine/DMD Clinics and Master of Science in Dentistry/MScD Clinics will be on face-to-face modality for Thursday and Friday. CDent classes will be online synchronous on both dates.

CAS Mla, CCSS, CEduc, and CEng'g Mla: Online Synchronous for Thursday and Asynchronous for Friday

CAS Cal., CBA Mla., CBA Cal., CEng'g Cal., and CFAD: Online Synchronous for Thursday and Friday

K to 12-Mla. and Cal. classes: Online Synchronous for Thursday and Friday

PE: Online Synchronous for Thursday (no PE classes on Fridays)

UE offices will be open during business hours as usual on these dates.

Thank you and take care, Warriors.

message.text:
UE Advisory
for Sept. 18 & 19, 2025

In light of the announced transport strike, please be advised of the following modalities for this Thursday and Friday, September 18 and 19, 2025 —

Graduate School and College of Law: Online modality for Thursday and Friday

CDent: Doctor of Dental Medicine/DMD Clinics and Master of Science in Dentistry/MScD Clinics will be on face-to-face modality for Thursday and Friday. CDent classes will be online synchronous on both dates.

CAS Mla, CCSS, CEduc, and CEng'g Mla: Online Synchronous for Thursday and Asynchronous for Friday

CAS Cal., CBA Mla., CBA Cal., CEng'g Cal., and CFAD: Online Synchronous for Thursday and Friday

K to 12-Mla. and Cal. classes: Online Synchronous for Thursday and Friday

PE: Online Synchronous for Thursday (no PE classes on Fridays)

UE offices will be open during business hours as usual on these dates.

Thank you and take care, Warriors.

message.text:
UE Advisory
for Sept. 18 & 19, 2025

In light of the announced transport strike, please be advised of the following modalities for this Thursday and Friday, September 18 and 19, 2025 —

Graduate School and College of Law: Online modality for Thursday and Friday

CDent: Doctor of Dental Medicine/DMD Clinics and Master of Science in Dentistry/MScD Clinics will be on face-to-face modality for Thursday and Friday. CDent classes will be online synchronous on both dates.

CAS Mla, CCSS, CEduc, and CEng'g Mla: Online Synchronous for Thursday and Asynchronous for Friday

CAS Cal., CBA Mla., CBA Cal., CEng'g Cal., and CFAD: Online Synchronous for Thursday and Friday

K to 12-Mla. and Cal. classes: Online Synchronous for Thursday and Friday

PE: Online Synchronous for Thursday (no PE classes on Fridays)

UE offices will be open during business hours as usual on these dates.

Thank you and take care, Warriors.

message.text:
#TamAnunsyo | As of September 15, 2025, the FEU Central Student Organization has formally submitted a recommendation letter in light of the upcoming nationwide transport strike announced by PISTON and MANIBELA on September 17–19, 2025.

Grounded on the results of the recent #TamsCheck Survey, the FEUCSO emphasized the need for proactive adjustments to safeguard student welfare and academic continuity. The recommendations include:

1. Shift to Online Modality during the strike dates
2. Leniency of Attendance for affected students
3. Extended Hours of University Facilities
4. Provision of Early and Clear Announcements

Check the full recommendation letter here: 

🔗: https://bit.ly/TransportStrikeRecommendationLetter

The FEUCSO remains committed to representing the concerns of the Tamaraw community and to engaging in constructive dialogue with the University for responsive and student-centered solutions.

Stay updated through our TamAnunsyo.

#TamaRiseTogether
#FEUCSO90

message.text:
#TamAnunsyo | As of September 15, 2025, the FEU Central Student Organization has formally submitted a recommendation letter in light of the upcoming nationwide transport strike announced by PISTON and MANIBELA on September 17–19, 2025.

Grounded on the results of the recent #TamsCheck Survey, the FEUCSO emphasized the need for proactive adjustments to safeguard student welfare and academic continuity. The recommendations include:

1. Shift to Online Modality during the strike dates
2. Leniency of Attendance for affected students
3. Extended Hours of University Facilities
4. Provision of Early and Clear Announcements

Check the full recommendation letter here: 

🔗: https://bit.ly/TransportStrikeRecommendationLetter

The FEUCSO remains committed to representing the concerns of the Tamaraw community and to engaging in constructive dialogue with the University for responsive and student-centered solutions.

Stay updated through our TamAnunsyo.

#TamaRiseTogether
#FEUCSO90

message.text:
#TamAnunsyo | As of September 15, 2025, the FEU Central Student Organization has formally submitted a recommendation letter in light of the upcoming nationwide transport strike announced by PISTON and MANIBELA on September 17–19, 2025.

Grounded on the results of the recent #TamsCheck Survey, the FEUCSO emphasized the need for proactive adjustments to safeguard student welfare and academic continuity. The recommendations include:

1. Shift to Online Modality during the strike dates
2. Leniency of Attendance for affected students
3. Extended Hours of University Facilities
4. Provision of Early and Clear Announcements

Check the full recommendation letter here: 

🔗: https://bit.ly/TransportStrikeRecommendationLetter

The FEUCSO remains committed to representing the concerns of the Tamaraw community and to engaging in constructive dialogue with the University for responsive and student-centered solutions.

Stay updated through our TamAnunsyo.

#TamaRiseTogether
#FEUCSO90
